==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peril
<hw>Per"il</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧ril</ets>, fr. L. <ets>periculum</ets>,
<ets>periclum</ets>, akin to <ets>peritus</ets> experienced, skilled,
and E. <ets>fare</ets>. See <er>Fare</er>, and cf.
<er>Experience</er>.]</ety> <def>Danger; risk; hazard; jeopardy;
exposure of person or property to injury, loss, or
destruction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In <qex>perils</qex> of waters, in <qex>perils</qex> of
robbers.</q> <rj><qau>2 Cor. xi. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Adventure hard⟦br⟧
With <qex>peril</qex> great achieved.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>At one's peril</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>On
one's peril</b></col></mcol>, <cd>with risk or danger to one; at the
hazard of.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>On thy</xex> soul's <xex>peril</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Hazard; risk; jeopardy. See
<er>Danger</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peril</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peril
<hw>Per"il</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Periled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or <conjf>Perilled</conjf>; <pos>p.
